flowRoot.flowPara: Another organization wants to join you and replicate the codebase (add that actor card).
You have had some work done to make the system 100% GDPR compliant.
Who will take responsiblity for that it actually is?
Public organization 2 has a large language minority and wants to make the interface multilingual. Others are unsure of how this will impact their workflow.
Public organization 2 lost their funding for working with the codebase. If they leave the shared costs will increase for you.

Public organization 2 went ahead and contracted a developer to add a new feature (add independent developer actor card)) without informing you. They make a pull request to add that feature to the codebase. How is that handled?

A feature introduced by Public organization 2 has a bug. The bug causes you problems, and you aren't even using this feature. It happens just before a big holiday, causing overtime. How can that situation be resolved?
Public organization 2 feels like all their issues in the backlog are not getting any attention at all and feels like their voice is not being heard (add backlog object card).
How will their complaint be addressed?
